This paper deals with micro-architectural attacks and cache side-channel attacks, which are typically studied in the computer security (cs.CR) and computer architecture (cs.AR) sub-categories. The paper also presents novel algorithms based on group testing, which is a topic in computer science theory (cs.DS). The empirical evaluation of the algorithms involves identifying factors that affect their reliability in practice, which falls under the software engineering (cs.SE) and programming languages (cs.PL) sub-categories.
